[{"id":"FT547981","type":"longtextV2","stimulusHtml":"Let <em>h</em> be the function given by <em>h(x)</em> =<em>kx</em>(1 - <em>x</em>) for . For each <em>k</em> &gt; 0, the region (not shown) enclosed by the graphs of <em>h</em> and <em>g</em> is the base of a solid with square cross sections perpendicular to the <em>x</em>-axis. There is a value of <em>k</em> for which the volume of this solid is equal to 15. Write, but do not solve, an equation involving an integral expression that could be used to find the value of <em>k.</em>","features":[{"type":"sharedpassage","html":"<p><img alt=\"A graph plots the curves of two functions. The graph of y equals f of x is a concave downward curve that begins at the origin, rises to a maximum point in the first quadrant, falls through the point 1 comma 0 into the fourth quadrant. The graph of y equals g of x is a concave upward curve that begin at the origin, falls down to a minimum point in the fourth quadrant nearer to the y axis, and further rises through the point 1 comma 0 into the first quadrant. The curves intersect at the point 1 comma 0. The region bounded by the  curves and the point of intersection is shaded.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/media.academicmerit.com/1436772991c07b9d61a6aa711e4524cc/original.jpg\" /></p>\n\n<p>Let <em>f</em> and <em>g</em> be the functions given by <em>f(x)</em> = 2<em>x</em>(1 - <em>x</em>) and&nbsp;<span aria-label=\"g of x is equal to 3 open paren x minus 1 close paren square root of x\"><math> <mrow> <mi>g</mi> <mrow> <mo>(</mo> <mi>x</mi> <mo>)</mo> </mrow> <mo>=</mo> <mn>3</mn> <mrow> <mo>(</mo> <mrow> <mi>x</mi> <mo>−</mo> <mn>1</mn> </mrow> <mo>)</mo> </mrow> <msqrt> <mi>x</mi> </msqrt> </mrow> </math></span> for&nbsp; <span aria-label=\"0 is less than or equal to x comma x is less than or equal to 1\"><math> <mrow> <mn>0</mn> <mo>≤</mo> <mi>x</mi> <mo>≤</mo> <mn>1</mn> </mrow> </math></span>. The graphs of <em>f</em> and <em>g</em> are shown in the figure above.</p>\n"}]}]